The paper focuses on the detection and tracking of dynamic objects in a changing environment using lightweight sensors, which is a key feature for autonomous behavior in robotics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper utilizes a segmentation approach based on median filters and an efficient pipeline for detection and tracking of small objects within sparse point clouds, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper also mentions an application for filtering the dynamic and mapping the static part of the data, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
